ximately half\nthat measured from Damped Lyman-$\\alpha$ Absorption (DLA) systems at $z \\gtrsim\n2$. Deeper surveys with existing and upcoming instruments will be critical to\nunderstand the evolution of $\\Omega_{\\rm HI}$ in the redshift range\nintermediate between $z \\sim 0.4$ and the range probed by DLA observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 May 2016 17:04:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-27"}
