\nbands. In Cd$_3$As$_2$, a distinctive peak in reflectivity due to the\nlogarithmic divergence in $\\epsilon_1$ expected at the onset of Dirac cone\ninterband transitions is identified. The center frequency of the peak shifts\nwith temperature quantitatively consistent with a linear dispersion and a\ncarrier density of $n=1.3\\times10^{17}\\text{ cm}^{-3}$. The peak width gives a\nmeasure of the Fermi velocity anisotropy of $10\\%$, indicating a nearly\nspherical Fermi surface. The lineshape gives an upper bound estimate of 7 meV\nfor the potential fluctuation energy scale.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 7 May 2016 05:59:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 May 2016 02:12:40 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 5 Jul 2016 16:05:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-08-17"}
